text: The teh-peng can be quite inconsistent — sometimes it’s perfectly balanced between the tea and condensed milk, but other times it tastes bland.
Wanted a not so usual dinner and found this ngoh hiang stall. Not too bad considering this is not easily available nowadays. Just that the sauce doesn’t give it much kick.

Superb Teh and Kopi here. Though it's made by their machine, it guarantees consistency on the mixture--which is always rich and of the right sweetness.

The Fishball Noodle or Mushroom Minced Meat Noodle is the stall that is mostly frequented by people here. Obvious with it's long queue all the time. Just wish they can have a way to manage it better or get the orders faster via online or qr code ordering. But then again, it's an old school coffeeshop so understandable.
The bak chor mee / laksa store has horrible attitude. Counter talks as if she hasn't been paid in years. Ranting off and muttering under her breath instead of conveying the message directly

Lack of seating. Long Q at some stalls especially weekends and holidays. Braised Duck rice quality dropped. Fishballs soup is more popular during breakfast hours. LorMee is another popular stall that has long Q.
